The paper proposes a novel solution for semi-supervised video object segmentation, which is a problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also leverages memory networks and machine learning techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with video data, which could place it in cs.MM (Multimedia) or cs.RO (Robotics).
